 [<span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎חָדַר‎</span>] **verb** ==surround, enclose== (Phoenician in derivatives; Arabic <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> II. ***conceal***, <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> ***curtain*** concealing a person, ***chamber, house, or tent*** as concealing some one; Ethiopic <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> ***dwell***; see also following) **\*\***Phoenician is only <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎חדר‎</span>, <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎חדרת‎</span> (temple or sepulchral) ***chamber*** (Lzb<sup>271</sup> Cooke<sup>126</sup>); [[Ezek.21.19|Ezek 21:19]] is best explained from Syriac <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> ***go about, surround***, Syriac ***around.*** It seems uncertain whether <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎חֶדֶר‎</span>, Phoenician <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎חדר‎</span> ***chamber***, Arabic <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> ***curtain, chamber, tent***, etc., are (ultimately) from this √ (as something ***surrounding***); or (Buhl) from II. <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎חדר‎</span> = <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> II. ***conceal behind curtain, conceal, confine***, IV. ***conceal oneself***, also ***abide, stay, remain behind*** (Land<sup>707 f.</sup>), Ethiopic <img class="bdbSeriacGlyph" src="data:image/gif;base64,"> ***abide, dwell*** (Driver, privately, Nov. 1905). — only **Qal** **Participle** feminine singular <span class="bdbLangHebrew">‎הַחֹדֶ֫רֶת לָהֶם‎</span> [[Ezek.21.19|Ezek 21:19]] ***that which surroundeth them*** (of the sword), — so [[BDB#Syr|ᵑ6]] [[BDB#Thes|Thes]] [[BDB#Sm|Sm]] [[BDB#Co|Co]] [[BDB#Da|Da]] [[BDB#VB|VB]].
